8. Camera Permission

Our app requests access to your device Camera (android.permission.CAMERA) for the following purpose:
To allow users to capture photos or videos within the app.
To enable features such as scanning, image uploads, or documentation.

Important:
The camera is only accessed when you actively choose to use a camera-related feature.
We do not access your camera in the background.
We do not record or capture images without your knowledge.
If captured images are uploaded (if applicable):
They are uploaded securely.
They are used only to provide app functionality.
They are not shared with third parties except as required to deliver the service.
If images are stored locally:
They remain on your device unless you explicitly choose to upload them.


